# Force LF line endings in the repo regardless of the checkout machine's
# core.autocrlf setting. Without this, cloning on Windows with the common
# `core.autocrlf=true` setting rewrites .sh files to CRLF, which breaks the
# shebang line (#!/bin/bash) when Git Bash tries to execute them.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf

*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.svg text eol=lf
*.ico binary
